      "role": "user",
      "content": "i was just looking at the stars and it hit me so hard... like, everything we do, every single thing we struggle for, it's all just a tiny blip in a cold, dead universe that doesn't even know we're here. it feels so pointless. why even bother trying to stay afloat when the end result of everything is just entropy and nothingness regardless?",
